# Patch 0012 — Universal search (PLATFORM_PLAN.md MVP item 5; ADR 0004).
#
# One query surface over everything local: open tabs, history, bookmarks,
# workspace notes, and downloads. Opened from the command palette action
# "Search Everything"; centered panel, keyboard-first (type, arrows, Enter;
# Escape closes). Results grouped by source, workspace-badged where a result
# belongs to a space; activating a tab result switches space if needed.
#
# ARCHITECTURE (ADR 0004 — federated, not indexed): each source is queried
# through its existing store — Places (nsINavHistoryQuery, frecency-sorted)
# stays authoritative for history/bookmarks, tabs are live gBrowser state,
# notes come through gZenWorkspaces.kavachaGetAllNotes() (single JSONFile
# owner), downloads via Downloads.getList. No new database; the Phase 6
# personal content index will plug in as one more source behind the same
# {title, detail, workspaceId, score, action} contract. URL-level dedup
# across sources: tab beats bookmark beats history.
#
# Mechanics, for future maintenance:
#   - Window module loaded via ZenPreloadedScripts.js scripts list
#     (chrome://browser/content/zen-components/KavachaUniversalSearch.mjs).
#   - Panel markup lives in zen-panels/popups.inc; the stylesheet is loaded
#     per window with windowUtils.loadSheetUsingURIString (AUTHOR_SHEET).
#   - XUL panels are native popup widgets: they do NOT appear in
#     window.drawWindow / Marionette screenshots — verify with computed
#     styles and rects, not pixels.
#   - Palette action registered in ZenUBGlobalActions.sys.mjs; strings in
#     zen-command-palette.ftl + zen-workspaces.ftl.
# Known follow-ups: dedicated keyboard shortcut (Zen kbs table), workspace
# filter toggle, Phase 6 content-index source.
# Applies on top of 0011.
